PicoARC license notice

This repository uses a split license:

- Hardware design materials are licensed under the CERN Open Hardware Licence
  Version 2 - Weakly Reciprocal (CERN-OHL-W-2.0).
- Firmware and general project documentation are licensed under the MIT License.

The repository-level license expression is:

    CERN-OHL-W-2.0 AND MIT

Hardware design materials include the schematic/netlist source, local hardware
components and modules, PCB layout, fabrication and assembly outputs, hardware
3D models, and hardware documentation under `hardware/`, unless a file states a
different license. The Source Location for the hardware design is this
repository.

Firmware materials include the project firmware source, build scripts, and
firmware documentation under `firmware/`, unless a file states a different
license. Third-party files, generated files, vendored dependencies, SDK files,
and imported snippets retain their own notices and license terms.

The full license texts are included in:

- `LICENSES/CERN-OHL-W-2.0.txt`
- `LICENSES/MIT.txt`
